Carnage/ Dinobot

*Carnage looked at the flying island and shook her head, there was no way in 
the Inferno that Teltoli could ever get her to it. She sighed.*


" I don't know, we could try. But I don't think it'll work too good."

*Carnage looked at the flying island, no, it wasn't too far. But she had a 
weight to her that she was trained to have, a weight that was needed to 
carry large weapons and win battles. The sort of weight an assassin needs in 
order to survive.
She thought that if Teltoli stayed in her beast mode and Carnage just hung 
onto her legs they just might be able to get to the island. But if it didn't 
work then it would have to be Cyber Claw who took Teltoli the rest of the 
way and not her, Carnage would just have to give her the coordinates, that's 
all.
Carnage sighed again, but there was no harm in trying.*

**************************************************************

*Dinobot snarls in surprise as Scourge's blade cuts across his face, right 
in the last place that Tavatron happened to slash in their training. An 
eruption of mech fluid comes from  the wound on impact and sprays outward, 
covering anything within a few steps.
He growled as he stepped back and shook his head, the mech fluid now seemed 
to spill from the wound and onto the ground. The wound was a large jagged 
slash from the top of his temple to a few millimeters from his chin, the 
mech fluid flowed down his neck, arm and chest.
Dinobot wiped the mech fluid from his optics as he looked Scourge straight 
in the optics, he could taste his own fluid and he spat.
He growled at Scourge as he took another step back, he had to think of 
something that he could do that would take this bot down!
Dinobot took a quick look towards Tavatron, she seemed to be unscathed by 
the surrounding battle...him on the other hand.
He judged the distanse of Scourge from him and saw that he was only a metre 
or two away, he growled and took a step forward, targeting with his site and 
aimed at the Predacon's optic again.
Dinobot then lept into the air and brought his claws down onto the 
Predacon's shoulders, with a quick action he swept them inward and towards 
his enemies neck. He knew that it was a risky move but he had to at least 
stop this one from entering the Ark....at any cost!*
